2. Sensor Alignment & Calibration
The MPU6500 mounted on the modular perfboard setup will likely have an incorrect default orientation.  

Navigate to the Setup tab.

Physically rotate the drone frame. The 3D model on the screen must perfectly mirror the physical Pitch, Roll, and Yaw movements.

If the movement is misaligned, navigate to the Configuration tab and locate the Board and Sensor Alignment section.  

Adjust the First Gyro orientation (e.g., CW 90°, CW 270°, or modifying Roll/Pitch degrees) until the 3D model accurately reflects the physical 250mm frame.  

Place the drone on a completely flat surface and click Calibrate Accelerometer.



3. Receiver Setup
To establish communication between the FlySky FS-i6 and the ESP32-S3 SuperMini:

Navigate to the Ports tab.

Enable Serial RX for the specific UART port wired to the receiver's signal pin. Click Save and Reboot.  

Navigate to the Receiver tab.

Change the Receiver Mode to Serial-Based Receiver.  

Change the Serial Receiver Provider to IBUS. Click Save.  

Power on the transmitter and verify the channel bars respond correctly to stick inputs.

4. Motor Calibration & Direction
The SimonK 30A ESCs utilizing the standard PWM protocol instead of a digital protocol like DShot, require a manual throttle range calibration so all A2212 motors start simultaneously.
Safety Warning: Strictly ensure all propellers are removed before proceeding.  

Unplug the LiPo battery. Keep the USB connected.

Navigate to the Motors tab.

Toggle the "I understand the risks" switch.  

Drag the Master Slider to the absolute maximum position (usually 2000).  

Plug in the LiPo battery. The ESCs will emit a musical tone or series of beeps, registering the high throttle mark.  

Immediately drag the Master Slider back down to the minimum position (usually 1000).  

The ESCs will beep again, confirming the low throttle mark is set and calibration is complete.  

Slowly raise each motor slider individually to verify the motors are spinning in the exact direction indicated by the diagram in Betaflight. If a motor spins backward, swap any two of the three wires connecting that specific motor to its ESC.  

5. Flight Modes
Navigate to the Modes tab.

Assign the ARM mode to a designated two-position switch on the transmitter.  

Assign the ANGLE mode (self-leveling) to an additional switch. Utilizing ANGLE mode is critical for stabilizing initial test flights.

